p: There were no significant differences on the mean number of eggs laid on oviposition substrate treated with ULV of G. procumbens and the control, either after 5 days (6.4 ± 2 and 7.4 ± 0.9 eggs), 10days (23.6 ± 1.5 and 27.4 ± 2.2 respectively) or 15 days (31.2 ± 2.44 and 32.6 ± 2.66), after the treatment respectively ( Fig. 10). Finally, no significant differences were observed between the treated substrate with R. officinalis and the control after 5 days of observation (1.6 ± 1.1. and 3.6 ± 1.3), but only 10 (8.6 ± 2.8 and 29.4 ± 1.2eggs) and 15 days (11.2 ± 3.6 and 33.2 ± 1.7) after the treatments.
